"content":"Bake for 75 minutes (250°F) or until meringues are dry with a creamy color. <strong>Do not open the oven door<\/strong> while meringues are baking to avoid collapsing."},{"content":"Once done, turn off oven and allow meringues to cool in oven until outsides crack slightly (approx. 2 hrs. or overnight). Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and make Sabayon Crème."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Sabayon Crème"},{"content":"Place sugar and lemon peel into mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>."},{"content":" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Add egg yolks and wine and cook <b>9 min\/160°F\/speed 3<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Quickly transfer Sabayon Crème to a bowl and set aside to cool."},{"content":" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place whipping cream into mixing bowl and without setting a time whisk <b>speed 3<b>, until stiff peaks form. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Using a large metal spoon, gently fold whipped cream into cooled egg yolk mixture until thoroughly combined."},{"content":"Top each cooled Meringue Cloud Cake with a ¼ cup fresh berries and ⅓ cup Sabayon Crème. Garnish with fresh basil leaves and serve immediately."}],"basicInfo":["medium","45m","4h 50m","6 portions"]}